                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.21/494: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-20T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 16 10 A.M.</p>
                <p>Department regrets condition described. You may assure President Suarez of our
                    sympathetic appreciation of his position and say that the treaty situation is
                    not without hope here, provided an early agreement may be reached as to the
                    protocol.</p>
                <p>Department expects soon to telegraph regarding idea suggested your despatch 112
                    of August 8<note n="29" xml:id="d746fn29">Not printed.</note> and telegram of
                    September 9 [<hi rend="italic">4?</hi>], 3 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
